// https://www.shadertoy.com/view/4cXfW7 chiral combined cuboid construct, 2024 by jt
// based on https://www.shadertoy.com/view/4ffBWn chiral combined cuboid cityscape
// repeated and mirrored // https://www.shadertoy.com/view/McffzM chiral combined cube composition
// visualized using https://www.shadertoy.com/view/lXGGR3 raymarch voxels with color

// Using DDA-raymarch hybrid approach to fill a voxel-grid sparsely
// with random chirally subdivided cubes, mirrored along coordinate axes
// (which achived combining cuboids into irregular forms).

// Cube subdivided into:
// a random core cuboid, two axial cuboids, two times three chiral cuboids.
// Reflections along each axis achieve continuity but constrain overall shape severely.
// Some parts have been replaced by frames to show internal structure.

// Structure resembles relaxed
// https://www.shadertoy.com/view/4cffWr space filling cube and half cube

// Note that the chiral components always overlap.
// Treating the three back chiral components and the axis components as solid
// while treating the three front chiral components as empty space,
// there is always a spiral path from the bottom to the top of the structure
// which would be useful if the structure were to be used
// in level design for a computer game (imagine ladders up the walls).

// tags: cube, subdivision, composition, unit, combined, chiral, dda, voxel, hybrid

